To bump:
  cd dashboard/vendor
  rm -rf ats-scrapers
  gh api repos/kalil0321/ats-scrapers/tarball/<new-sha> > t.tgz
  tar xzf t.tgz && mv kalil0321-ats-scrapers-* ats-scrapers && rm t.tgz
  # then update commit / commit_date / vendored_at above
  # and re-run the smoke test:
  uv run --directory dashboard/vendor/ats-scrapers jobhive --help

CLI shape (as of pinned SHA):
  jobhive list-ats                 # ATS coverage from upstream manifest
  jobhive scrape <ats> <company>   # scrape ONE company on ONE ATS
  jobhive search                   # query the published dataset
  jobhive publish                  # publish CSVs to R2 (upstream only)

Note: there is no "scrape all companies on ATS X" CLI subcommand. The
shim that Gate 4 introduces uses jobhive as a Python library to iterate
ats-companies/<ats>.csv inside a single long-lived subprocess per ATS,
rather than spawning one subprocess per company.
